.TH "ABSTRACTRANGE.STARTCONTAINER" "3JS" "January 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
AbstractRange.startContainer \- AbstractRange: startContainer property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]startContainer\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]AbstractRange\f[R] interface returns the \f[CR]Node\f[R] in which
the start of the range is located.
.PP
To change the start position, use the \f[CR]Range.setStart()\f[R] method
or a similar one.
.SH VALUE
The \f[CR]Node\f[R] inside which the start position of the range is
found.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] range = document.createRange();
range.setStart(startNode, startOffset);
range.setEnd(endNode, endOffset);

\f[B]const\f[R] startRangeNode = range.startContainer;
.EE
